<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><listPerson xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><person xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="HIB01" sex="1"><persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><roleName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/><forename xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Julian</forename><surname xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Hibbert</surname><addName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></persName><birth xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1801"><placeName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></birth><death xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1834-01-24"/><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">writer</occupation><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">reformer</occupation><note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="editorial"><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Hibbert was a known republican and a recognised Greek scholar. He visited Richard Carlile (1796-1843) in Dorchester prison and gave him £1000. Carlile had been 
    imprisoned for seditious libel in 1819. Hibbert refused to take the oath when later appearing as a witness in a case due to his atheism which caused outrage to the court. 
    This in turn was said to have caused his death some days later. The <title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Morning Chronicle</title> for 28 January 1834 reported: ‘The deceased was known as a violent Republican. He 
      was the person who appeared at the Old Bailey the session before last to give a character to a German named Berhold, 
    who was convicted of a felony, and excited the disgust of the Court and spectators by boldly avowing 
    himself to be an Atheist and speaking contemptuously of the Holy Scripture….it appears he dies in 
    a fit of apoplexy.’</p>
  
  In 1830 Hibbert wrote to Godwin saying that he would be keen to undertake the education (for his amusement) of a youth, but he 
  does not want to throw away his time on anyone who is not going to have an independent fortunewith a fortune, such as Godwin's grandson Percy.  They had not previusly met.  Godwin declined the offer.
  
